verbose_text: Adjusting for age, hypertension, dyslipidemia, and history of smoking, low-dose aspirin significantly reduced primary end points in patients with eGFR 60-89 mL/min/1.73 m 2 (0.53 [0.34-0.83]; P = 0.0052), and not in patients with eGFR> = 90 or < 60 mL/min/1.73 m 2 (eGFR> = 90 mL/min/1.73 m 2 : 0.87 [0.36-2.14]; eGFR < 60 mL/min/1.73 m 2 : 1.24 [0.69-2.23]).
